These cross-currents showed how the same administration could promote openness where it served its narrative\'97unsealing Epstein records under a law it had championed\'97while suppressing economic data and attacking independent media elsewhere. The trait \'93memory curated by power\'97what cannot be controlled is erased\'94 rose slightly, because the pattern was not of blanket secrecy, but of selective illumination and shadow. Public health information followed a similar path. Robert F. Kennedy Jr., as health secretary, had dismissed the entire prior immunization advisory committee and installed vaccine skeptics. Under this new panel, the CDC\'92s Advisory Committee on Immunization Practices delayed and then voted to limit universal hepatitis B vaccination for newborns, recommending that most parents consult a doctor rather than receiving the shot automatically at birth. This marked the first time in decades that access to a routine childhood vaccine was restricted in this way. The decision, taken against a long record of evidence about the vaccine\'92s benefits, signaled a shift from science-based policy toward politicized risk framing, with potential long-term effects on disease prevention.\
